      Who is going to keep track of the point system?  Any volunteers.  This is just like trying to keep track of a attendance schedule of people...when they show up and leave...etc.  It can be very hard and frustrating.  Also, usually the people do it don't like to just sit there and do that...so there are going to be some mad mistakes I'm sure.  <br>
<br>
Another thing, who has a compilation of all people in the guilds so that we can appropriately donate the first 6 points to each person.  I think we should test this out a few raids before we lay down any groundwork on it....cause it's going to be a bitz to get used to also.  Plus your going to have to kepe the list out in the open so people can see how many points they have...etc.  <br>
<br>
Who wants to write the html to throw up a link to this on the webpage also...should it be pworded so only members can get into it...or we just going to leave it out in the open for all to see.  <br>
<br>
What about people with 2 toons...maybe I skipped this above.  Most commonly I play 2 toons on planar raids usually...cyph for damage...rhonin for cr's. <br>
<br>
I feel PoG should not recieve any points for going since all can't attend.  It would really suck to be a ranger and other people getting more points then you on a zone that you cannot attend in.  I mean...who really wants to run around and track mobs so other people can get xp/drops?  I sure wouldn't want to for just a few points.<br>
<br>
Just a little input I thought I'd throw in.  This is a good start...but lots of little issues need to be gone over before we just lay this into effect.  Nice start though Dine.<br>
Cyphonic<br>
