<br>
The point pool per toon is probably the best option so we are comparing apples to apples, or in this case, so my necro isn't spending my warriors points against other necros.<br>
<br>
What about people that are running more than one toon per raid simultaneously?  Bren I know sometimes runs Gath when the raid runs late and he has to go to bed.  Will points per toon cover that sufficiently?<br>
<br>
The only thing that is missing is what constitutes a points raid.  We were saying 3+ groups, but should we put an advanced notice limit on things?  To qualify to be a points raid it has to be posted at least 3 days in advance maybe?<br>
<br>
Example, we get a wild hair on a slow night and decide to do a spur of the moment kedge raid.  Phinny is up and we wanna take him out &lt;hands napkin to Bren&gt;, we probably need more horsepower than can be mustered just with the OBS online, so we put out the call to DS.  It is a slow night for you guys too and there are only a few online, we manage to get a couple of people to show up, but only 2 or 3, and the rest of the say 4 groups are OBS.  Or if the situation is reversed with DS doing the impromptu and OBS not fielding many if any.  Does that make a points raid?<br>
<br>
What if it is posted for however long and one or the other guild either doesn't show at all or shows with only a couple of people?  Still points raid?<br>
<br>
I am not bitching, just thinking out loud.<br>
Az<br>
